<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Boot1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Boot,</orth> subst., covering for the foot and leg; particularly worn by horsemen: <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.2.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. V, 2, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 45</bibl> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.1.147" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 147</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.5.39" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 5, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 3.2.6" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.3.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 3, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.2.77" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 2, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.1.91" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 1, 91</bibl> (quibble). <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.68" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 68</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.270" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 270</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.3.136" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 136</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.177" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 177</bibl>. Used by fishermen: <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.5.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 5, 101</bibl>. <cit><quote>over --s in love,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.1.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. I, 1, 25</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>give me not the --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.1.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. I, 1, 27</bibl></cit>, == do not make a laughing-stock of me (allusion to the torture of the boots?).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>